    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.13"/>
                
                <note>
                    Ans.&#8212;.2-9-72
                    dictated
                </note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        January 27, 1972
                        1119 North Elm 
                        Hastings 
                        Nebraska 68901
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine street<sic>Street</sic></addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Nebraska 68100</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Thank you so very much for agreeing to do this dedication for me, the Society will rejoice in this too when they hear of it. I have only told them that a notable Nebraskan of those days will write it for us hoping you would do it.</p>
                
                <p>It can be a printed page or a little more if you wish, and it should stress the values, honesty, a man's word was as good as his bond, compassion for each other, you will know being of that caliber yourself. Yes, I knew of your experience in a soddy so please mention that as you did in the letter, and how long ago it was. Our membership area includes this whole section up into Canada, we have no state boundaries, wherever there were soddies, there we have members. Particularly Kansas, Nebraska, and the Dakotas, Wyoming and Colorado, Montana, etc.</p>
                
                <p>My deadline is a week or so from now, but if you find yourself too rushed, any time within the first two weeks of February will be soon enough. I have been working so hard on the short history, the negro section and other myriad details that I left the dedication and the acknowle<del>g</del><add>d</add>gements and front of the book plan until the last. Yes, I appreciate how busy you must be and am looking forward to seeing the autobiography, it will be fascinating to me. You are such a complicated personality, forgive me for saying this, but really it is a compliment you know, that I find myself how one person can have so many varied facets.</p> 
                
                <p>Anyway, thank you right from my heart.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Cordially yours,</salute> 
                
                    <signed>Frances Jacobs Alberts</signed>
                    <signed>Frances Jacobs Alberts</signed> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
